docs.lead_paragraph: The Executive Committee of the American Tract Society has completed the appropriation of $20,000 for operations in foreign countries. The receipts of the Society during the last month were $35,139, and for eleven months to March 1, $316,204.

docs.lead_paragraph: Gossip says, perhaps prematurely, that the Empress EUGENIE will not suffer the direct line of the BONAPARTES to fail. We are without political news. Three new Senators have been added to the list-Gen. AUPICK, the French Ambassador at Madrid, M. LEBRUN, ex-Peer of France and Baron THIEULLEN, member of the Corps Legislatif.

docs.lead_paragraph: Suddenly, on Friday, March 25, WILLIAM T. BLAGROVE, in the 45th year of his age. The friends of the family are invited to attend his funeral on Saturday, at 2 o'clock, P. M., from No. 115 Atlantic-st., Brooklyn.

docs.lead_paragraph: ENFORCING ORDINANCES.--His Honor Mayor LAMBERT has gone to work in good earnest to en force all the ordinances of the City, particularly those affecting in any way the health of the City. He is very well supported by the police in this effort for the general good, and every day numerous arrests are made of parties violating ordinances which have heretofore been but partially, if at all, enforced.

docs.lead_paragraph: To the Editor of the New-York Daily Times: Delineations of character, such as I am drawing, are, for their effect, helped by parallel, provided it be not too formal or too forced. A real and well-managed contrast of trait with trait, serves, like well-distributed light and shade in a picture, to make the figures set off' each other.

headline.main: FATHER GAVAZZI IN NEW-YORK.; PROTESTANT MEETING OF WELCOME. Speeches from Rev. Dr. Cox, Rev. Dr. Cheever, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: In pursuance of a numerously signed public notice addressed to "The Friends of Civil and Religious Liberty," a large assemblage convened in the Tabernacle, last evening, for the purpose of welcoming to the United States Father GAVAZZI, the celebrated Roman patriot and orator.

docs.lead_paragraph: The proposed General Law for organizing Life and Health Companies is not called for by sound policy. At least such a bill as the one now before the Assembly is not. It is wholly inadequate to any safe purpose.
